function J = costFunction (X,y, theta)

m = rows(X);    #determine the number of rows or amount of training data

predicted = X * theta;

Sqrderrors = (y - predicted) . ^2;    #determine the squared difference in each set of data from predicted and actual

J = 1/(2*m) * sum(Sqrderrors);      #determine the J value, which is trying to be minimally optimzed
